# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GridMind — real cloud-cost integrations (ALL read-only)
#
# Copy to .env.local and fill in only the providers you use. GridMind reads your
# billing/usage to power the dashboard and recommendations. It NEVER launches,
# stops, drains, or bids on anything, never moves money, and never changes your
# cloud configuration. These credentials live only in your environment — the app
# does not store, transmit, or display them. Grant the minimum read-only scope.
#
# After editing, restart the dev server and open /integrations → "Sync now".
# With nothing set, GridMind runs on a built-in sample fleet.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Amazon Web Services — Cost Explorer (read-only) ──────────────────────────
# IAM permission required: ce:GetCostAndUsage  (nothing else)
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
AWS_REGION=us-east-1
# Optional: cost-allocation tag key used to break spend down by team.
GRIDMIND_AWS_TEAM_TAG=
# Optional kill-switch: set to "off" to ignore AWS even if keys are present.
GRIDMIND_AWS=

# ── Microsoft Azure — Cost Management (read-only) ────────────────────────────
# Role required: "Cost Management Reader" on the subscription.
# Create an app registration (service principal) for these values:
AZURE_TENANT_ID=
AZURE_CLIENT_ID=
AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET=
AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID=

# ── Google Cloud — BigQuery billing export (read-only) ───────────────────────
# 1) Enable Cloud Billing export to BigQuery.
# 2) Service account needs: BigQuery Data Viewer + BigQuery Job User on that dataset.
GCP_PROJECT_ID=
GCP_SA_EMAIL=
# Paste the private key with literal \n escapes (as it appears in the JSON key file).
GCP_SA_PRIVATE_KEY=
# Fully-qualified billing export table, e.g. project.dataset.gcp_billing_export_v1_XXXX
GCP_BILLING_TABLE=

# ── Neoclouds (CoreWeave, Lambda, etc.) — generic read-only cost feeds ───────
# JSON array of cost feeds. Each feed returns [{day,cost,region?,gpu?,gpuHours?}].
# providerId should match a catalog id (coreweave, lambda, …).
# Example:
# GRIDMIND_NEOCLOUD_FEEDS=[{"id":"coreweave","providerId":"coreweave","url":"https://api.example.com/cost","key":"ro_xxx"}]
GRIDMIND_NEOCLOUD_FEEDS=
